<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,301,1487]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[198,330,1341,1366]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honor of Batu, the great military leader who commanded the Golden Horde, an allusion to the dense golden setae present on the dorsum of the head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,301,1487]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis box="[198,301,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species, known only from the female, keys with some difficulty and appears in the key in two locations.
</paragraph>
